com.avanza.astrix.core

Annotation Type AstrixPartitionedRouting


  • @Target(value=PARAMETER)
 @Retention(value=RUNTIME)
 @Documented
public @interface AstrixPartitionedRouting
    Indicates that a remote invocation request should be partitioned and routed on a given argument. The argument must be a subclass of Collection, or an array type. The request will be partitioned by splitting the request into one request against each server partition containing only the arguments in the target collection that are routed to the given server partition.
    Author:
    Elias Lindholm (elilin)

    • Optional Element Summary

      Optional Elements 
      Modifier and Type Optional Element and Description
      Class<? extends Collection> collectionFactory
      Factory used to create instances of the partitioned argument Collection.
      Class<? extends RemoteResultReducer> reducer
      AstrixRemoteResultReducer to use to reduce the response from each server partition into a return value.
      String routingMethod
      If defined, then the given method will be invoked on each element in the target collection to decide what partition a given element should be routed to.

    • Element Detail

      • routingMethod

        public abstract String routingMethod
        If defined, then the given method will be invoked on each element in the target collection to decide what partition a given element should be routed to. The target method must take zero arguments and have non-void return type.
        Returns:
        Default:
        ""

      • reducer

        public abstract Class<? extends RemoteResultReducer> reducer
        AstrixRemoteResultReducer to use to reduce the response from each server partition into a return value.

        Default:
        com.avanza.astrix.core.DefaultAstrixRemoteResultReducer.class

      • collectionFactory

        public abstract Class<? extends Collection> collectionFactory
        Factory used to create instances of the partitioned argument Collection. Default to ArrayList. If ArrayList is not a compatible type for the given argument then this property must be set to a Class that is compatible with the partitioned argument container. The Class must have a zero argument constructor.
        Default:
        java.util.ArrayList.class
